# Cursor AI Rules for HFSO100_to_AnninAR4_connector

# PRIMARY DOCUMENTATION
# Read llms.txt for complete system architecture and rules!

# CODE STYLE
- Follow existing project conventions (snake_case for Python)
- Maximum line length: 100 characters
- Use type hints where applicable
- Document complex kinematics/transformations thoroughly

# CRITICAL RULES (from llms.txt)
1. NEVER add kinematics to Leader node (only raw joint angles)
2. ALWAYS communicate in Cartesian space between robots
3. MAINTAIN RobustPolicy.forward() structure for LeRobot compatibility
4. USE non-blocking ZMQ (NOBLOCK, CONFLATE) for real-time control
5. APPLY transforms in order: FK → SWAP → MIRROR → OFFSET → SAFETY → IK

# FILE ORGANIZATION
- Executable nodes: package/scripts/
- Hardware drivers: package/drivers/SO100_Robot/
- Kinematics: package/drivers/SO100_Robot/so100_core/
- Config/URDF: package/drivers/SO100_Robot/config/

# DEBUGGING
- Use DualLogger for simultaneous stdout and file logging
- Log Cartesian coordinates before and after transforms
- Check ZMQ message format: {"joints": [...], "gripper": float}

# TESTING
- Test safety limits (safe_z, safe_x) before deploying
- Verify URDF loads correctly (check paths)
- Validate coordinate transforms with known positions
